  "course_description": "Focused survey of modern art in Europe with an emphasis on aesthetic, social, and historical dimensions of modernist practices. Movements include Fauvism, Expressionism, Cubism, Futurism, Dada, Constructivism, and Surrealism. Writings by artists and critics will be considered in relation to the art.",
  "course_notes": "Art in Paris: Matisse, Picasso, Bonnard This course will focus on avant-garde art in Paris from around 1907 - when Picasso painted his infamous Demoiselles d'Avignon and Matisse his Blue Nude - to the years preceding World War II, when Matisse began his extraordinary series of cut-outs. At the center of the course will be the achievements of three massively influential artists: Picasso, Matisse, and Pierre Bonnard. Art History major/minor: Division III",
